idth%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%20photo%20illustration.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66991be349138fa6f6e360cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20results%20of%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman's%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20study%20are%20in.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOverall%20spending%20increased%2C%20but%20most%20of%20the%20extra%20cash%20went%20to%20food%20and%20rent.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERecipients%20noted%20decreased%20financial%20stress%2C%20but%20that%20faded%20over%20time%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20are%20in%20for%20Sam%20Altman's%20much-anticipated%20basic%20income%20study%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20of%20its%20kind.%20The%20experiment%20gave%20low-income%20participants%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20three%20years%2C%20no%20strings%20attached.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecipients%20put%20the%20bulk%20of%20their%20extra%20spending%20toward%20basic%20needs%20like%20rent%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20food%2C%20the%20study%20found.%20They%20also%20worked%20less%20on%20average%20but%20remained%20engaged%20in%20the%20workforce%20and%20were%20more%20deliberate%20in%20their%20job%20searches%20compared%20to%20a%20control%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRecipients%20had%20greater%20agency%20to%20make%20decisions%20that%20worked%20best%20for%20their%20lives%20and%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20future%2C%20from%20moving%20neighborhoods%20to%20expressing%20interest%20in%20new%20business%20ventures%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report's%20authors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20a%20leading%20artificial%20intelligence%20company%2C%20raised%20%2460%20million%20for%20the%20study%2C%20including%20%2414%20million%20of%20his%20own%20money.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.openresearchlab.org%2Fapproach%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20the%20study%2C%C2%A0which%C2%A0was%20led%20by%20researcher%20Elizabeth%20Rhodes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20officially%20began%20in%202019%20when%203%2C000%20Texas%20and%20Illinois%20residents%20across%20urban%2C%20suburban%2C%20and%20rural%20areas%20enrolled.%20All%20of%20these%20residents%20had%20incomes%20below%20%2428%2C000.%20A%20third%20got%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20three%20years%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20%E2%80%94%20the%20control%20group%20%E2%80%94%20got%20%2450%20a%20month.%20No%20enrolled%20participants%20lost%20their%20existing%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20those%20who%20received%20the%20%241%2C000%20payments%20increased%20their%20overall%20spending%20by%20an%20average%20of%20%24310%20a%20month%2C%20but%20most%20of%20that%20spending%20went%20toward%20food%2C%20rent%2C%20and%20transportation.%20They%20also%20offered%20more%20financial%20support%20to%20others%20in%20need%20compared%20to%20the%20control%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%2C%20however%2C%20said%20they%20found%20no%20%26quot%3Bdirect%20evidence%20of%20improved%20access%20to%20healthcare%20or%20improvements%20to%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%26quot%3B%20among%20those%20who%20received%20%241%2C000%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20see%20significant%20reductions%20in%20stress%2C%20mental%20distress%2C%20and%20food%20insecurity%20during%20the%20first%20year%2C%20but%20those%20effects%20fade%20out%20by%20the%20second%20and%20third%20years%20of%20the%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20could%20only%20do%20so%20much.%20%26quot%3BCash%20alone%20cannot%20address%20challenges%20such%20as%20chronic%20health%20conditions%2C%20lack%20of%20childcare%2C%20or%20the%20high%20cost%20of%20housing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f9fd84cd-91cb-426e-86a2-3a3a6135eb76%5C%22%3EThe%20debate%20over%20basic%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20inspired%20by%20Altman's%20belief%20in%20the%20importance%20of%20a%20basic%20income%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI%2C%20which%20some%20fear%20could%20render%20millions%20of%20jobs%20obsolete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20impossible%20to%20truly%20have%20equality%20of%20opportunity%20without%20some%20version%20of%20guaranteed%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20said%20when%20announcing%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-people-spend-universal-basic-income-ubi-food-housing-transportation-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euniversal%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20around%20for%20awhile%2C%20but%20rose%20to%20prominence%20as%20the%20center%20of%20Andrew%20Yang's%202016%20presidential%20campaign.%20Other%20significant%20figures%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%20have%20since%20voiced%20support%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20some%20kind%20of%20basic%20income%2C%20including%20Twitter%20cofounder%20Jack%20Dorsey%20and%20Tesla%20CEO%20Elon%20Musk.%20AI%20godfather%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-godfather-geoffrey-hinton-universal-basic-income-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGeoffrey%20Hinton%20recently%20advised%20the%20British%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20adopt%20a%20universal%20basic%20income%20to%20mitigate%20the%20number%20of%20%26quot%3Bmundane%20jobs%26quot%3B%20AI%20is%20set%20to%20replace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20universal%20basic%20income%20would%20provide%20all%20people%20with%20direct%20cash%20payments%2C%20no%20strings%20attached.%20That's%20a%20hefty%20political%20lift%2C%20however.%20So%20many%20cities%20and%20states%20have%20experimented%20with%20guaranteed%20basic%20incomes%20instead.%20These%20programs%20provide%20cash%20payments%20without%20restrictions%20to%20select%20low-income%20or%20vulnerable%20populations.%20Altman's%20study%20falls%20into%20this%20camp%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20dozens%20of%20these%20smaller%20programs%20have%20found%20that%20cash%20payments%20can%20help%20alleviate%20homelessness%2C%20unemployment%2C%20and%20food%20insecurity%20%E2%80%94%20though%20results%20still%20stress%20the%20need%20for%20local%20and%20state%20governments%20to%20invest%20in%20social%20services%20and%20housing%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Altman%20also%20floated%20another%20kind%20of%20basic%20income%20plan%2C%20which%20he%20called%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-sam-altman-universal-basic-income-idea-compute-gpt-7-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAltman%2520has%2520long%2520supported%2520a%2Cas%2520AI%2520threatens%2520their%2520jobs.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euniversal%20basic%20compute%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20In%20this%20scenario%2C%20Altman%20said%20people%20would%20get%20a%20%26quot%3Bslice%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20computational%20resources%20of%20large%20language%20model%20GPT-7%2C%20which%20they%20could%20use%20however%20they%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20own%20part%20of%20the%20productivity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Fall-in-with-chamath-jason-sacks-friedberg%2Fid1502871393%3Fi%3D1000655220554%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20these%20smaller%20experiments%2C%20however%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-opposition-discriminatory-universal-basic-income-argument-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efaced%20political%20hurdles%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Conservatives%20in%20several%20states%20have%20challenged%20the%20programs%2C%20halting%20their%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228ac87517-0da8-463d-9395-bf25b14d1489%5C%22%3EThe%20Altman%20study's%20findings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20results%2C%20Altman's%20study%20assessed%20both%20quantitative%20data%2C%20such%20as%20surveys%20and%20bank%20transactions%2C%20and%20qualitative%20data%2C%20such%20as%20interviews%20with%20recipients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20compared%20to%20the%20control%20group%2C%20recipients'%20total%20individual%20savings%20in%20their%20bank%20accounts%20increased%20by%20nearly%2025%25.%20Recipients%20also%20spent%20%2422%20more%20a%20month%20on%20other%20people%2C%20or%20about%2026%25%20more%20than%20the%20control%20group.%20There%20was%20little%20impact%20on%20car%20or%20home%20ownership%2C%20though%20recipients%20of%20the%20%241%2C000%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20move%20neighborhoods%20or%20pay%20for%20housing%20than%20the%20control%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegarding%20healthcare%2C%20recipients%20saw%20slight%20increases%20compared%20to%20the%20control%20group%20in%20dental%20care%2C%20emergency%20room%20visits%2C%20and%20healthcare%20spending%20%E2%80%94%20though%20there%20was%20no%20direct%20evidence%20of%20improved%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecipients%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20have%20a%20budget%20and%20advance%20their%20education%2C%20specifically%20in%20the%20third%20year%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20control%20group.%20However%2C%20there%20were%20no%20significant%20effects%20on%20educational%20attainment%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20which%20began%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20when%20unemployment%20was%20high%2C%20found%20that%20employment%20rates%20fell%20in%20the%20second%20and%20third%20years%20among%20recipients%20compared%20to%20the%20control%20group.%20On%20average%2C%20incomes%20rose%20significantly%20for%20all%20groups%2C%20though%20slightly%20higher%20for%20the%20control%20group.%20Incomes%20for%20recipients%20of%20the%20%241%2C000%20rose%20from%20just%20under%20%2430%2C000%20to%20%2445%2C710%2C%20while%20incomes%20for%20the%20control%20group%20started%20at%20a%20similar%20level%20but%20grew%20higher%2C%20to%20%2450%2C970.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCash%20offers%20flexibility%20and%20may%20increase%20agency%20to%20make%20employment%20decisions%20that%20align%20with%20recipients'%20individual%20circumstances%2C%20goals%2C%20and%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report's%20authors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278870e8c-3763-4a7c-a1d2-a8d6bae99891%5C%22%3EWhat%20the%20participants%20in%20Altman's%20basic%20income%20study%20say%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20recipient%20in%20the%20program%2C%20Sarah%2C%20is%20a%20mother%20of%20four%20from%20rural%20Illinois%20who%20teaches%20in%20a%20homeschool%20network%20and%20makes%20just%20enough%20from%20her%20job%20to%20pay%20for%20school%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20really%20make%20anything%20off%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20testimonial%20shared%20by%20OpenResearch.%20%26quot%3BEven%20though%20my%20husband%20had%20a%20pretty%20decent%20job%2C%20we%20didn't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20for%20extras.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20payments%20from%20the%20Altman%20program%20helped%20Sarah%20pay%20for%20braces%20for%20both%20of%20her%20children%2C%20which%20weren't%20covered%20by%20their%20insurance%2C%20she%20said.%20She%20also%20used%20the%20money%20to%20finance%20a%20graduation%20trip%20for%20her%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Sarah%20said%20she%20began%20%26quot%3Bslipping%20into%20a%20mindset%26quot%3B%20where%20she%20was%20less%20careful%20with%20her%20finances%20because%20it%20felt%20like%20money%20was%20coming%20in%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20having%20to%20work%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLooking%20back%2C%20I%20regret%20that%20I%20didn't%20save%20more%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20recipient%2C%20Cara%2C%20told%20the%20study's%20researchers%20that%20she%20suffered%20from%20a%20debilitating%20nerve%20disorder%20that%20caused%20pain%20across%20much%20of%20her%20body%20and%20a%20loss%20of%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20started%20to%20receive%20some%20short-term%20disability%20payments%2C%20she%20said%20a%20break-in%20to%20her%20apartment%20set%20her%20back%20financially%2C%20and%20she%20began%20to%20sell%20her%20personal%20belongings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFeeling%20the%20loss%20of%20being%20able%20to%20care%20for%20yourself%20and%20desperately%20needing%20the%20help%20of%20others%3B%20it's%20rough%2C%26quot%3B%20Cara%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20started%20crying%26quot%3B%20when%20she%20got%20the%20phone%20call%20saying%20she%20would%20be%20receiving%20%241%2C000%20payments%20from%20the%20Altman%20program.%20The%20money%20helped%20her%20pay%20off%20nearly%20all%20of%20her%20debts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20like%20a%20miracle%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BKnowing%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20manage%20that%20mountain%20of%20medical%20debt%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20my%20brain%20would%20have%20been%20in%20a%20completely%20different%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECelene%2C%20another%20participant%2C%20told%20researchers%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20move%20her%20family%20in%20with%20a%20friend%20after%20losing%20money%20in%20a%20business%20venture.%20She%20said%20she%20was%20living%20in%20squalid%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20received%20the%20call%20that%20she%20had%20been%20selected%20for%20the%20group%20receiving%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20she%20was%20in%20utter%20disbelief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20money%20helped%20her%20buy%20new%20clothes%2C%20shoes%2C%20and%20basic%20necessities%20for%20herself%20and%20her%20children.%20By%20the%20second%20month%2C%20she%20had%20landed%20a%20job%20and%20began%20saving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20money%20helped%20her%20%26quot%3Bnot%20feel%20like%20a%20failure%20as%20a%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20and%20gave%20her%20the%20confidence%20to%20make%20decisions%20in%20her%20family's%20best%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altma