%20during%20a%20Senate%20term%20and%20as%20Biden's%20second-in-command.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20running%20against%20Republican%20candidate%20Donald%20Trump%20she%20would%20also%20have%20a%20major%20vulnerability%20-%20a%20troubled%20situation%20at%20the%20U.S.-Mexico%20border%20that%20has%20bedeviled%20Biden%20and%20become%20a%20top%20campaign%20issue.%20Harris%20was%20tasked%20at%20the%20start%20of%20his%20term%20with%20addressing%20the%20root%20causes%20of%20high%20irregular%20migration%2C%20and%20Republicans%20have%20sought%20to%20make%20her%20the%20face%20of%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20range%20of%20global%20priorities%2C%20said%20analysts%2C%20a%20Harris%20presidency%20would%20resemble%20a%20second%20Biden%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20may%20be%20a%20more%20energetic%20player%20but%20one%20thing%20you%20shouldn't%20expect%20-%20any%20immediate%20big%20shifts%20in%20the%20substance%20of%20Biden's%20foreign%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Aaron%20David%20Miller%2C%20a%20former%20Middle%20East%20negotiator%20for%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20administrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20has%20signaled%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20that%20she%20would%20not%20deviate%20from%20Biden's%20staunch%20support%20for%20NATO%20and%20would%20continue%20backing%20Ukraine%20in%20its%20fight%20against%20Russia.%20That%20stands%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20a%20pledge%20by%20former%20president%20Trump%20to%20fundamentally%20alter%20the%20U.S.%20relationship%20with%20the%20alliance%20and%20the%20doubts%20he%20has%20raised%20about%20future%20weapons%20supplies%20to%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EStaying%20On%20The%20Course%20On%20China%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lawyer%20by%20training%20and%20a%20former%20California%20attorney%20general%2C%20Harris%20struggled%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20Biden's%20term%20to%20find%20her%20footing%2C%20not%20helped%20by%20being%20saddled%20early%20on%20with%20a%20major%20part%20of%20the%20intractable%20immigration%20portfolio%20amid%20record%20crossings%20at%20the%20U.S.-Mexico%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20followed%20a%20failed%202020%20presidential%20campaign%20that%20was%20widely%20considered%20lackluster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20she%20becomes%20the%20nominee%2C%20Democrats%20will%20be%20hoping%20Harris%20will%20be%20more%20effective%20at%20communicating%20her%20foreign%20policy%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20second%20half%20of%20Biden's%20presidency%2C%20Harris%20-%20the%20country's%20first%20Black%20and%20Asian%20American%20vice%20president%20-%20has%20elevated%20her%20profile%20on%20issues%20ranging%20from%20China%20and%20Russia%20to%20Gaza%20and%20become%20a%20known%20quantity%20to%20many%20world%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20year's%20Munich%20Security%20Conference%20she%20delivered%20a%20tough%20speech%20slamming%20Russia%20for%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20pledging%20%26quot%3Bironclad%26quot%3B%20U.S.%20respect%20for%20NATO's%20Article%205%20requirement%20for%20mutual%20self-defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20China%2C%20Harris%20has%20long%20positioned%20herself%20within%20Washington's%20bipartisan%20mainstream%20on%20the%20need%20for%20the%20U.S.%20to%20counter%20China's%20influence%2C%20especially%20in%20Asia.%20She%20would%20likely%20maintain%20Biden's%20stance%20of%20confronting%20Beijing%20when%20necessary%20while%20also%20seeking%20areas%20of%20cooperation%2C%20analysts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20has%20made%20several%20trips%20aimed%20at%20boosting%20relations%20in%20the%20economically%20dynamic%20region%2C%20including%20one%20to%20Jakarta%20in%20September%20to%20fill%20in%20for%20Biden%20at%20a%20summit%20of%20the%20Association%20of%20Southeast%20Asian%20Nations%20(ASEAN).%20During%20the%20visit%2C%20Harris%20accused%20China%20of%20trying%20to%20coerce%20smaller%20neighbors%20with%20its%20territorial%20claims%20in%20the%20disputed%20South%20China%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20also%20dispatched%20Harris%20on%20travels%20to%20shore%20up%20alliances%20with%20Japan%20and%20South%20Korea%2C%20key%20allies%20who%20have%20had%20reason%20to%20worry%20about%20Trump's%20commitment%20to%20their%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20demonstrated%20to%20the%20region%20that%20she%20was%20enthusiastic%20to%20promote%20the%20Biden%20focus%20on%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Murray%20Hiebert%2C%20a%20senior%20associate%20of%20the%20Southeast%20Asia%20Program%20at%20Washington's%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20could%20not%20match%20the%20%26quot%3Bdiplomatic%20chops%26quot%3B%20Biden%20had%20developed%20over%20decades%2C%20%26quot%3Bshe%20did%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20like%20her%20boss%2C%20Harris%20has%20been%20prone%20to%20the%20occasional%20verbal%20gaffe.%20On%20a%20tour%20of%20the%20Demilitarized%20Zone%20between%20South%20and%20North%20Korea%20in%20September%202022%20to%20reassert%20Washington's%20support%20for%20Seoul%2C%20she%20mistakenly%20touted%20a%20U.S.%20%26quot%3Balliance%20with%20the%20Republic%20of%20North%20Korea%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20aides%20later%20corrected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Harris%20becomes%20her%20party's%20standard-bearer%20and%20can%20overcome%20Trump's%20lead%20in%20pre-election%20opinion%20polls%20to%20win%20the%20White%20House%2C%20the%20Israel-Palestinian%20conflict%20would%20rank%20high%20on%20her%20agenda%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20Gaza%20war%20is%20still%20raging.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20as%20vice%20president%20she%20has%20mostly%20echoed%20Biden%20in%20firmly%20backing%20Israel's%20right%20to%20defend%20itself%20after%20Hamas%20carried%20out%20a%20deadly%20cross-border%20raid%20on%20Oct.%207%2C%20she%20has%20at%20times%20stepped%20out%20slightly%20ahead%20of%20the%20president%20in%20criticizing%20Israel's%20military%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20she%20bluntly%20criticized%20Israel%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20not%20doing%20enough%20to%20ease%20a%20%26quot%3Bhumanitarian%20catastrophe%26quot%3B%20during%20its%20ground%20offensive%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20enclave.%20Later%20that%20month%2C%20she%20did%20not%20rule%20out%20%26quot%3Bconsequences%26quot%3B%20for%20Israel%20if%20it%20launched%20a%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20refugee-packed%20Rafah%20in%20southern%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20language%20has%20raised%20the%20possibility%20that%20Harris%2C%20as%20president%2C%20might%20take%20at%20least%20a%20stronger%20rhetorical%20line%20with%20Israel%20than%20Biden%2C%20analysts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20her%2081-year-old%20boss%20has%20a%20long%20history%20with%20a%20succession%20of%20Israeli%20leaders%20and%20has%20even%20called%20himself%20a%20%26quot%3BZionist%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%2C%2059%2C%20lacks%20his%20visceral%20personal%20connection%20to%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20maintains%20closer%20ties%20to%20Democratic%20progressives%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20have%20pressed%20Biden%20to%20attach%20conditions%20to%20U.S.%20weapons%20shipments%20to%20Israel%20out%20of%20concern%20for%20high%20Palestinian%20civilian%20casualties%20in%20the%20Gaza%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20analysts%20do%20not%20expect%20there%20would%20be%20a%20big%20shift%20in%20U.S.%20policy%20toward%20Israel%2C%20Washington's%20closest%20ally%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHalie%20Soifer%2C%20who%20served%20as%20national%20security%20adviser%20to%20Harris%20during%20the%20then-senator's%20first%20two%20years%20in%20Congress%2C%20from%202017%20to%202018%2C%20said%20Harris'%20support%20of%20Israel%20has%20been%20just%20as%20strong%20as%20Biden's.%20%26quot%3BThere%20really%20has%20been%20no%20daylight%20to%20be%20found%26quot%3B%20between%20the%20two%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIran%20Nuclear%20Threat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20could%20also%20be%20expected%20to%20